<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n43094d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n43" href="#n43094d">N43 (VI.B.35)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n43all.htm#n43094d"> 94(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> uncials / cursives</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Miniscule letters are cursive (<i>i.e.</i> running) forms of the curved letters about an inch long called &ldquo;uncials&rdquo; (from Latin <i>uncia</i>, &ldquo;an inch,&rdquo; or from <i>uncus</i>, &ldquo;crooked&rdquo;). <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA2"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 37 [Memory-aids and Picture-writing]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
